m_q.target_metric: Cluster labels for customer groups based on behavioral features
sub_questions: What features should represent customer behavior?
How to handle customers with limited transactions?

schema_conflicts: InvoiceDate dtype differs: object in CSV vs datetime64[ns] in Excel
Year 2010-2011.csv contains data from 2010-2011, not just 2009-2010

scale_issues: Customer ID is float but should be categorical
cross_source_conflicts: Year 2010-2011.csv includes 2011 data which should be excluded per question
online_retail_II.xlsx appears to duplicate Year 2009-2010.csv data

format_notes: InvoiceDate format varies: '12/1/2009 7:45' in CSV vs '2009-12-01 07:45:00' in Excel
Description field contains quotes and commas
Country values may have leading/trailing spaces

constraints: Customer ID must not be null
Output file must be named cluster.csv
Output columns: Feature_i (for feature values) and Cluster (cluster label)
statistical_tests: Check for outliers in Quantity and Price
Determine optimal number of clusters using elbow method/silhouette score
output_format_requirements: Column names: Feature_1, Feature_2, ..., Feature_n, Cluster
